Reasoning: The paper deals with fine-grained visual categorization, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new feature learning framework, which involves sparse coding and dictionary updating, indicating that it may fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of local orientation histograms, which suggests that it may be relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
